This paper deals with the identification of web servers based on their response codes, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the data, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the current state of web infrastructure, which could be classified under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
